  "id": "019d286c-c8e3-7462-a4e5-a639c4c2371c",
  "content": "### Task 3.3: Implement `CoverageGap` check\n\n\n```rust\nfn check_coverage_gap(entries: &[KnowledgeEntry]) -> Vec<Finding> {\n    let memory_only: Vec<_> = entries.iter()\n        .filter(|e| e.metadata.content_role.as_deref() == Some(\"memory\"))\n        .collect();\n    let has_formal = entries.iter().any(|e| {\n        matches!(e.metadata.content_role.as_deref(), Some(\"design\" | \"decision\" | \"plan\"))\n    });\n\n    if !memory_only.is_empty() && !has_formal {\n        vec![Finding::new(\n            CheckType::CoverageGap,\n            &entries[0].scope_id,\n            memory_only.iter().map(|e| e.id).collect(),\n            0.7,\n            format!(\n                \"{} memory entries found but no design/decision/plan docs — consider formalizing\",\n                memory_only.len()\n            ),\n        )]\n    } else {\n        Vec::new()\n    }\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Run tests**\n\nRun: `cd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia && cargo test -p corvia-kernel test_coverage_gap -- --nocapture`\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia\ngit add crates/corvia-kernel/src/reasoner.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(reasoner): implement CoverageGap check for memory-only topics\"\n```\n\n---\n",
